Key Match Events: Pascal Siakam scored 26 points in the Indiana Pacers' 129-113 victory over the Chicago Bulls.
Thomas Bryant added a season-high 22 points and eight rebounds.
Tyrese Haliburton had 16 points and 13 assists.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Indiana Pacers won their fourth straight game, all by 10 or more points.
The Pacers continued climbing the Eastern Conference standings with their 10th win in 13 games.
